translated: Åhmansson, Olov Wood, engineer, born on 25/6/99 in Gothenburg to engineer John Robert and Margaret Åhmansson. Married on 29/xx to Ingeborg Brisman. Children: Laila, born in 1937. Studied at Parkdale College Institute in Toronto, Canada. Graduated from Chalmers University of Technology in 1925. Worked in England, Scotland, and was involved in patenting at the Swedish Tubing Factory A-B Ljungström in Finspång from 1925-1928. Became the head of the patent department at SKF from 1928. Wrote various articles on patents and trademarks.
